text: Dick Renooy (15 July 1908 â€” 24 July 1983) was a Dutch motorcycle road racer from Soest. Renooy competed in the 125cc class on his Eysink motorcycle. He had international successes. He is in the Netherlands most known for winning the Dutch TT in 1948. After an illness, Renooy died in early August in 1983 at the age of 75. == References == == Other websites == * Newspaper articles of Renooy, via Delpher Category:1900s births Category:1983 deaths Category:Dutch motorcycle racers
